item.description: … where I come from. I am cold, out waiting for the day to come – by Joanna Newsom Credit: Photo taken by Shawn Anderson (Seattle)

item.title: Sawdust and Diamonds
item.description: And the moment I slept, I was swept up in a terrible tremor Though no longer bereft, how I shook! And I couldn’t remember Then the furthermost shake drove a murthering stake in And cleft me right down through my center And I shouldn’t say so, but I knew that it was then, or never – by Joanna Newsom Credit: Photo taken by Daniel Arnold
